by XPC-HR23B is lesion independent. Furthermore, we reveal that TFIIH
inhibits the structure-specific endonuclease activities of both XPG
and ERCC1-XPF, responsible for the 3' and 5' incision in NER, respectively.
The inhibition occurs in the absence of ATP and is reversed upon
addition of ATP. These results point toward additional roles for
TFIIH and ATP during NER distinct from a requirement for DNA unwinding
in the regulation of the endonuclease activities of XPG and ERCC1-XPF.},
