the first NER stages, and suggest a two-step mechanism of damage
recognition involving damage detection by XPC-HR23B followed by damage
verification by XPA. This provides a plausible explanation for the
extreme damage specificity exhibited by global genome repair. In
analogy, in the transcription-coupled NER subpathway, RNA polymerase
