found that human RPA bound specifically and directly to two excision
repair proteins, the xeroderma pigmentosum damage-recognition protein
XPA (refs 8, 9) and the endonuclease XPG (refs 10-13). Although it
had been suggested that RPA might function before the DNA synthesis
repair stage, our finding that a complex of RPA and XPA showed a
