resides at the 3' side. Polarity appears crucial for positioning
of the excision repair nucleases XPG and ERCC1-XPF on the DNA. With
the 3'-oriented side of hRPA facing a duplex ssDNA junction, hRPA
interacts with and stimulates ERCC1-XPF, whereas the 5'-oriented
