extracts was present in the intact nine-subunit form. There was no
evidence for a repair complex that contained all of the NER components.
At low ionic strength TFIIH could associate with functional amounts
of each NER factor except RPA. At physiological ionic strength, TFIIH
associated with significant amounts of XPC-HR23B and XPG but not
other repair factors. The strongest interaction was between TFIIH
and XPC-HR23B, indicating a coupled role of these proteins in early
steps of repair. A panel of antibodies was used to estimate that
there are on the order of 10(5) molecules of each core NER factor
per HeLa cell.},
